ell_type":"code","source":"df <- read.csv('/kaggle/input/homicides/homicide-data.csv')\nhead(df)\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:11.332633Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:11.334661Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:11.734974Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Through this Data set ,\n* Distribution of the Age and identifying Min, Max, and Quantiles for ages.\n* Distribution of ages by victim race and contribution of victims by race.\n* To see the contribution of victim's gender by Races.\n* To identify which location has reported the most cases and to identify the most cases reported in which year.\n* To identify the trend of victim cases over time.\n* To identify the most dangerous area.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Investigating and Summarizing the data set","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"summary(df)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:15.226672Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:15.228478Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:15.497282Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Checking on the first and last 5 Rows in the data set**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"cat(\"First 5 rows in the data Set\", \"\\n\")\ndf[1:5,]\ncat(\"\\n\")\ncat(\"Last 5 rows in the data set\", \"\\n\")\ndf[-(1:52174),]","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:17.392692Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:17.394599Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:17.465479Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# After going through the Data Set","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* Data frame: 52,179 Observations(rows) and 12 Variables(columns)\n* Variables: From variables, 9 variables are characters, one is an integer, and the other two variables are numbers (double)\n* Missing Values: lat : Latitude variable has 60 missing data(NA). lon : Longitude variable is 60 missing data(NA).\n* Data type: reported_date: date format is 20100504 . Need to convert to the appropriate format. Victim_age: Data type is character. Need to convert to the integer.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Checking for unique categories in victim_race, victim_sex, state and disposition","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df_checking <- df[,c(5,7,9,12)]\ncolname <- colnames(df_checking)\n\nfor(col in colname)\n{\n    uniques_values <- unique(df[,col])\n    unique_counts <- length(unique(df[,col]))\n    cat(\"Unique categories for \",col, \"(\", unique_counts,\")\",\"\\n\" )\n    cat(\"Unique values are : \",uniques_values,\"\\n\\n\")\n}","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:20.803018Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:20.80488Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:20.843487Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"I see here **wI** instead of **WI**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Cleaning the Data Set","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"na_counts <- colSums(is.na(df))\nna_counts","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:23.364703Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:23.366534Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:23.392377Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"We see here only lat and lon has missing values.But, I see reported_date and victim_age . After we change to the correct data type we  may receive na values.\nWe can check it . First we need to convert to the data type.\n* Here I start with repoted_date - Converting to the Date data type","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df$reported_date <- ymd(df$reported_date)\n# checking  how many na columns has generated after change the data type of the Date\nna_counts <- colSums(is.na(df))\nna_counts\n# Now I see two na missing data under reported_date\n\n# I want see which observations has the problem\nproblem_rows_rpt_date <- df[is.na(df$reported_date),]\nproblem_rows_rpt_date","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:27.019378Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:27.021136Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:27.268773Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* Move on to the victim_age","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df$victim_age <- as.numeric(df$victim_age, na.rm = TRUE)\nna_counts <- colSums(is.na(df))\nna_counts","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:30.164908Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:30.166734Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:30.194485Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Now I see 2999 missing values in the victim_age's variable after convert to the number.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#Cheking few rows from the data set which has the missing data for victim_age\nproblem_rows_victim_age<- df[is.na(df$victim_age),]\nhead(problem_rows_victim_age)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:32.554232Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:32.55988Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:32.603882Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Now I'm going to drop all **\"na\"** from the data set","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df2 <- na.omit(df)\n# cheking again are there any missing values under variables\n\nna_counts <- colSums(is.na(df2))\nna_counts","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:49:59.645903Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:49:59.649259Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:49:59.912339Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"No missing vaules under the variables now","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"I'm going to change **wI** to **WI**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df2$state <- gsub(\"wI\",\"WI\",df2$state)\n\n# Checking unique values under State variable to make sure Data has been changed.\nunique(df2[,9])","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:49:59.921329Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:49:59.930853Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.01038Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Now It has been changed","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Analysis and Visualization","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":" Identifying Outliers","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"summary(df2)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.019082Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.025447Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.085854Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**I see min of victim_age is 0 and max of victim_age is 102**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"options(repr.plot.width = 30,repr.plot.height = 5 )","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.094137Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.10021Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.145512Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"ggplot(df2, aes(x = victim_age))+\nscale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,105,2))+\ngeom_boxplot()+labs(title = \"Distribution of Victim's Age\", x = 'Age')+\ntheme(plot.title = element_text(face = \"bold\", hjust = 0.5, size = 15),\n     axis.title.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.title.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.text.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10),\n     axis.text.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.162436Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:00.185739Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:02.600441Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"I assumed here victim_age is less than 3 and more that 64 people doesn't have phisical capability to do the victim. Then I'm gonna remove these age range people from the data set.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data_set<- df2 %>% filter(victim_age <= 64 & victim_age >3)\nana_data_set <- data.frame(data_set)\nsummary(ana_data_set)\n\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:02.60542Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:02.608588Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:02.705077Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**After Remove Ourliers**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"ggplot(data_set, aes(x=victim_age)) +\ngeom_boxplot()+\nscale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,80,2))+\nlabs(title = \"Distribution of Victim's Age\", x = 'Age')+\ntheme(plot.title = element_text(face = \"bold\", hjust = 0.5, size = 15),\n     axis.title.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.title.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.text.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10),\n     axis.text.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10))\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:02.724313Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:02.72997Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:03.960889Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Checking for victim_race and contribution**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"options(repr.plot.width = 10, repr.plot.height = 10)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:03.975766Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:03.978459Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.011062Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data_set %>% \nselect(victim_race) %>% \ngroup_by(victim_race)%>% \nsummarise(total_count = (count = n()))%>% \nggplot(aes(x=\"\", y = total_count, fill = victim_race ))+\ngeom_bar(stat = \"identity\",width = 6, color = 'white')+\ncoord_polar(\"y\", start =0)+\ngeom_text(aes(label =scales::comma(total_count)), position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5))+\nlabs(title = \"Total Victims By Race\", x = NULL, y = NULL)+\ntheme_minimal()+\ntheme(axis.text.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size =15))\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.016265Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.019239Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.771852Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Black people have been involved to victims that other races.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Visualizing Vitcim Race VS Victim Age in Box plot chart to check Age Distribution of all Races**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"options(repr.plot.width = 30)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.776681Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.779703Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.796228Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data_set %>% \nggplot(aes(x = victim_age, y = victim_race, fill = victim_race))+\ngeom_boxplot()+\nscale_x_continuous(breaks =seq(4,64,2))+\nlabs(title = \"Distribution of Victim Age by Race\",  x = \"Victim Age\", y = \"Victim Race\")+\ntheme_minimal()+\ntheme(plot.title = element_text(face = \"bold\", hjust = 0.5, size = 15),\n     axis.title.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.title.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.text.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10),\n     axis.text.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.800768Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:04.802672Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:06.691541Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* White people have the Highest median Age.\n* The lowest median age for Black race people.\n* Asian People and White people have a wider spread of the age.\n* Black people's ages clustered around 22 - 37 age.\n\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Cheking how many Female and male has involed in victims from all races**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data_set %>%\n  ggplot(aes(y = victim_race, fill = victim_sex)) +\n  geom_bar(stat = \"count\", position = \"dodge\") +\n  labs(title = \"Number of Victim's sex by Race\", y = \"Race\", x = \"Victims\")+\ntheme_minimal()+\ntheme(plot.title = element_text(face = \"bold\", hjust = 0.5, size = 15),\n     axis.title.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.title.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.text.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10),\n     axis.text.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:06.699196Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:06.704653Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:08.523138Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* Black Male has involved in victims than another Race's Male\n* Black Females have involved victims than another Race's Female\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Year <- year(data_set$reported_date)\n\ndata_set %>%\nggplot(aes(x = Year, fill =victim_sex ))+\nscale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(2007,2017,1))+\nscale_fill_manual(values = c(\"Male\" = \"gray28\", \"Female\" = \"seagreen\", \"Unknown\" = \"gold\")) +\ngeom_bar()+\ntheme_minimal()+\ntheme(plot.title = element_text(face = \"bold\", hjust = 0.5, size = 15),\n     axis.title.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.title.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 14),\n     axis.text.x = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10),\n     axis.text.y = element_text(face = \"bold\", size = 10))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:08.562579Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:08.564756Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:09.344641Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* I see in 2016 has reported most cases and in 2009 has reported less casesthan the other years","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"options(repr.plot.height = 10)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:09.349728Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:09.35204Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:09.381977Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data_set %>%\n  select(state) %>%\n  group_by(state) %>%\n  summarise(total_victims = n(), .groups = \"drop\") %>%\n  arrange(desc(total_victims)) %>%\n  ggplot(aes(y = reorder(state, total_victims), x = total_victims, fill = total_victims)) +\n  geom_bar(stat = \"identity\") +\n  scale_x_continuous(expand =c(0.005,0), breaks = seq(0,6000,250))+\n  labs(title = \"Total Victims by State\",\n       x = \"Total Victims\",\n       y = \"State\") +\n  theme_minimal() +\n  theme(\n      plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),\n        axis.title.y = element_blank(),\n        axis.text.y = element_text(vjust = 0, face = 'bold', size = 12),\n        axis.text.x = element_text(vjust = 0, face = 'bold', size = 12))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:09.387228Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:09.389123Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:10.024195Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* Most victims have reported in CA state.\n* After CA,  next two leading states for victims are IL and TX\n* Least cases have been reported in CO - Colarado","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"I'm going to look into deeply on the datas for state of CA , TX and IL.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"year <- year(data_set$reported_date)\n\ndata_set %>% \n    mutate(year) %>% \n    select(year, state)%>%\n    group_by(state,year)%>%\n    summarise(total_incident = n(), .groups = 'drop')%>%\n    filter(state %in% c(\"CA\", \"TX\", \"IL\"))%>%\nggplot(aes(x= year, y = total_incident,color = state)) +\n  geom_line(linewidth =1) +\n  theme_minimal() +\n  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(2007,2017,1))+\n  labs(title = \"Trend of victim cases for Top three States over the years\",\n       x = \"Year\",\n       y = \"Reported Cases\",\n       color = \"State\") +\n  scale_color_manual(values = c(\"CA\" = \"blue\", \"TX\" = \"green\", \"IL\" = \"red\"))+\n  theme(\n      plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),\n      axis.title.y = element_text(face = 'bold',size =14),\n      axis.title.x = element_text(face = 'bold',size =14),\n        axis.text.y = element_text(vjust = 0, face = 'bold', size = 12),\n        axis.text.x = element_text(vjust = 0, face = 'bold', size = 12),\n  legend.position = 'none')","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:10.02772Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:10.029632Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:10.596161Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Checking on the Status of the Disposition\n* I'm going to create a Pie chart to display this variable. This would help to see the contribution.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"data_set%>%\n    select(disposition)%>%\n    group_by(disposition)%>%\n    summarise(total_disposition = n())%>%\nggplot(aes(x =\" \", y =total_disposition, fill =disposition ))+\n    geom_bar(stat = \"identity\", width = 6, color = \"grey\")+\n    coord_polar(\"y\", start =0)+\n    scale_fill_manual(values = c(\"Closed without arrest\" = \"navy\",\"Closed by arrest\" = \"seagreen\",\"Open/No arrest\" = \"gray28\"  ))+\n    geom_text(aes(label =paste(total_disposition, \"\\n\",disposition)), position = position_stack(vjust =0.5), family = \"bold\", color = 'white', size = 6)+\n    labs(title = \"Total count of each Disposition category\", x =NULL, y = NULL)+\n    theme_minimal()\n\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-10T02:50:10.601196Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-10T02:50:10.603971Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-10T02:50:11.293943Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Still remaining more cases to solve. ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Through the Analysis","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* I analyzed homicide data which was generated for the period 2007 - 2017\n* The maximum age of the data set shows as 102 and the minimum shows as 0. - I see some Victim's ages are not possible to do the victim. It may be a typing mistake or wrong data collection. Should have some mental and physical strength to do the victim.\n* CA is the worst place according to the data set (most reported cases).\n* CO is the calm place according to the data set (least reported cases).\n* Victim_races = \"black\" is involved in most cases according to the data set information.\n* I don't see a huge gap through the year for the victims. But I can say most cases were reported in 2016 and the least cases were reported in 2009.\n* According to the data set's information 21748 remaining cases are still to be solved or to be arrested.\n\n","metadata":{}}]}